column5: Federal Register / Vol. 76, No. 123 / Monday, June 27, 2011 / Proposed Rules

column6: DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY / 10 CFR Part 430 / [Docket Number EERE–2011–BT–STD– 0011] / RIN 1904–AC06
Energy Conservation Program: Energy Conservation Standards for Residential Furnaces and Residential Central Air Conditioners and Heat Pumps

column5: 1/10/13 - BAW - efficiency & compatible system table revisions + addition of 2015 standard version
1/10/13 - SAC - reformat table to new syntax, combine standard versions into single table and add SysAvail & IsHP flags
5/20/13 - BAW -added ductless systems, Standard Design column
8/6/13 - SAC - added Show Multi-Speed Compressor column
9/3/2013 - MJB turned on more SysAvail options
column21: Need Std Design system col (especially for no cooling)

column5: 12/9/13 - specification of standard systems for Evap systems
4/22/14 - SAC - added PropEqStd column and also the new AirToWaterHeatPump & GroundSourceHeatPump equipment types
1/26/15 - MJB added rows for other Standards - e.g. 2008 Title-24 and 2006 IECC
1/7/16 - SAC - added rows for new SDHVSplitAirCond & SDHVSplitHeatPump (small duct, high velocity) systems
CodeBase - Standard or Code that should be used in the Std Design baseline

column8: Compliance 2014:  valid through December 2014 (with current Federal Air Conditioning efficiency requirements
Compliance 2015:  any time (with 2015 Federal Air Conditioning Requirements)  and solar credit

column5: COP95 - Gas Cooling Efficiency (rated COP for the gas portion)
PPC - Gas Cooling parasitic electric energy at rated conditions (in Watts)
SysAvail - (0/1) flag whether or not the system type is currently implemented in the compliance software
DuctFlag - 1 => requires ducts / 0 => ductless / -1 => may use ducts
IsHP - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not this system type is modeled as a heat pump
Whether or not (1/0) multi-speed compressor is an option
PropEqStd - flag indicating that the proposed design system is to be setup/modeled the same as its corresponding standard design system
StdSystem - system type used to model the standard design
SEERValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the SEER data is valid for the corresponding system type
EERValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the EER data is valid for the corresponding system type
